==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Müllerian
<hw>M⟦uum⟧l*le"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.,
Med.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or discovered by, <person>Johannes
<etsep>M⟦uum⟧ller</etsep></person>; <as>as, Mullerian duct; Muellerian
tumor; M⟦uum⟧llerian capsule</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>M⟦uum⟧llerian ducts</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>a
pair of embryonic ducts which give rise to the genital passages in the
female, but disappear in the male.</cd> -- <col><b>M⟦uum⟧llerian
fibers</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>the sustentacular or
connective-tissue fibers which form the framework of the
retina.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mullet</ent>⟦br⟧
